<br>
As it turns out, we knew a few of the same people, and in talking to one of them they'd asked how we met. After relating the incident, they laughed and said, &quot;Oh, that was you.&quot; Apparently I was the only person who ever answered that question honestly. Everyone else had either muttered &quot;I'm not lookin at anything.&quot; or had taken up the provocation to start something. (and it was intended as a provocation, after knowing him for a while, I'd seen him use it as a kind of intimidation/challenge)<br>
<br>
He's heavily tattoed, and does like to show off his artwork, but he recognizes it sets him apart, and revels in that difference.<br>
<br>
(Funny story, as it turns out, he was not only tatooed, but was a tattoo artist. Someone once came into his studio with &quot;Long Bech&quot; done in big gothic letters across his back, when asked if it could be fixed, Tom replied, &quot;You have a better chance of the city changing it's name.&quot;)<br>
<br>
Xethux <p>Confrontation is the essence of nature, confrontation is the rythm of life. In nature violence is pure and purposeful, one species against another an an act of survival.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrazakthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazak Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 320<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 3:39:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=587.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Judging</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
What I want to say is people should be judged for themselves, not clothes, not wieght, not hair, not tats, not piercings, but for what is inside<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, my definition of &quot;themselves&quot; is everything about them. Is a person's spirituality a part of them? Or is it some adornment they can leave in a closet? What about their sense of humor? What about their eye color? <br>
<br>
I look at a person, and I see the whole picture. I don't judge a person based only on their bad parts, or only on their good parts, but on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> whole</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> picture of the person. <br>
<br>
If a tatoo is to be ignored, why get one? I would think a tatoo would be something you would specifically want people to see, and thus you want people to notice it. To notice that it is a part of you. That your choice to get a tatoo is a part of what makes you, you. <br>
<br>
<br>
As for ignoring what's on the &quot;outside&quot; in favor or the &quot;inside&quot; - your body is the one thing that you must take with you everywhere. It is with you 24/7, wether you like it or not. It's your temple. It's your center. It is the place where all of your important things reside. Your heart, your mind, your spirit - they have to have some place to gather. Your body is your temple. <br>
<br>
As such, I try and respect mine. I don't exclude it because &quot;only what's on the inside counts&quot;. No, the container is just as important. If you don't take care of it, you won't be around to do anything with the rest of yourself. Your heart won't be around to love. Your mind won't be around to think. And your spirit won't be around to connect with everyone else. <br>
<br>
As for Tatoos - they don't do permanent damage, they aren't harmful to your health, and they don't damage your body. They are just an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> interesting</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> choice in art. Personally, they intrigue me. <br>
<br>
-Krazak <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=587.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=587.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=587.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=587.topic&index=24><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.threadControl?topicID=587.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=587.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=587.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionaviefrm58">Telegrams!<option value="firionaviefrm47">Guilds and Associations<option value="firionaviefrm10">A Bard for a Day<option value="firionaviefrm23">Hero Heart Tavern<option value="firionaviefrm15">The Polli